Note:
RADIX TREE - Compressed Prefix Tree Tier 0 Primitive

This file implements a binary radix tree (a.k.a. PATRICIA-trie variant)
where each edge stores a label (byte sub-string of the key) rather than
a single byte. Edge labels are compressed so that linear chains of
single-child nodes collapse into one edge.

The node uses linked-list children (each child knows its edge label)
rather than a 256-slot array so the memory footprint is proportional
to the number of distinct edges, not 256 * num_nodes. This gives much
better memory efficiency for sparse key spaces (IP prefix tables,
filesystem path tries, etc.).

Node structure (32 bytes):
  offset 0:  has_value flag (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  value (8 bytes)
  offset 16: first_child pointer (8 bytes; head of children linked list)
  offset 24: next_sibling pointer (8 bytes; used when this node is a child)

Edge label is stored adjacent: when a node is a child, its parent points
at it. The edge label associated with reaching this node is stored as
a separate allocation referenced by an "edge label" field. To keep the
node fixed-size, we store the edge label pointer in a second auxiliary
record co-allocated with the node:

  Each child slot is actually a "child entry" with:
    offset 0:  child node pointer (8 bytes)
    offset 8:  edge label pointer (8 bytes; null-terminated byte string)
    offset 16: edge label length (8 bytes)
    offset 24: next sibling entry pointer (8 bytes)

The root has an implicit empty edge label.

Header (16 bytes):
  offset 0: root node pointer
  offset 8: entry_count
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let RADIX_NODE_SIZE be 32
Let RADIX_EDGE_SIZE be 32
Let RADIX_HEADER_SIZE be 16

Note: ============================================================================
Note: NODE / EDGE CONSTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a fresh radix node with no children, no value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
32-byte alloc, zero-init by allocator suffices.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: 32 bytes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "radix_node_create" returns Integer:
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with RADIX_NODE_SIZE
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 24, 0
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning
Allocate a child edge entry. Stores the child node pointer, the edge
label byte pointer, and the label length. The label byte string is
heap-allocated and copied from the caller's buffer to give the radix
tree ownership.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) Allocate 32-byte edge entry.
2) Allocate (label_len + 1) bytes for the label, copy bytes plus null
   terminator.
3) Wire fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(label_len). Space: 32 + (label_len + 1) bytes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on any allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "radix_edge_create" takes child as Integer, label_src as Integer, label_off as Integer, label_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Let edge be proc allocate from Layout with RADIX_EDGE_SIZE
    If edge is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let label_alloc_size be label_len plus 1
    Let label be proc allocate from Layout with label_alloc_size
    If label is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with edge
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than label_len:
        Let src_addr be label_src plus (label_off plus i)
        Let b be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with src_addr, 0
        Let dst_addr be label plus i
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with dst_addr, 0, b
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Let term_addr be label plus label_len
    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with term_addr, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with edge, 0, child
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with edge, 8, label
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with edge, 16, label_len
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with edge, 24, 0
    Return edge
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TREE CONSTRUCTION / DESTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Create empty radix tree.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Header + root node.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "radix_create" returns Integer:
    Let tree be proc allocate from Layout with RADIX_HEADER_SIZE
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc radix_node_create
    If root is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with tree
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, root
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, 0
    Return tree
End Process

@Reasoning
Free every node, edge entry, and label allocation in the tree.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterative postorder. Maintain a work stack of node pointers. For each
popped node:
- Walk its child-edge linked list, pushing each child node onto the
  stack and freeing the edge label and edge entry.
- Free the node.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(N).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "radix_destroy" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    Let cap be 64
    Let buf_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
    Let buf be proc allocate from Layout with buf_bytes
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sp be 0
    If root is not equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, 0, root
        Set sp to 1
    End If
    While sp is greater than 0:
        Set sp to sp minus 1
        Let off be sp multiplied by 8
        Let node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf, off
        Let edge be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 16
        While edge is not equal to 0:
            Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 0
            Let label be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 8
            Let next_edge be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 24
            Let need be sp plus 1
            If need is greater than cap:
                Let new_cap be cap multiplied by 2
                Let new_bytes be new_cap multiplied by 8
                Let new_buf be proc allocate from Layout with new_bytes
                If new_buf is equal to 0:
                    proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                    Return 0
                End If
                Let copy_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
                proc memory_copy from Memory with new_buf, buf, copy_bytes
                proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                Set buf to new_buf
                Set cap to new_cap
            End If
            Let s_off be sp multiplied by 8
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, s_off, child
            Set sp to sp plus 1
            If label is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with label
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with edge
            Set edge to next_edge
        End While
        proc deallocate from Layout with node
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with buf
    proc deallocate from Layout with tree
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Entry count accessor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read entry_count at offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "radix_size" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: STRING HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Compute strlen for a null-terminated key.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Loop until null byte.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must supply null-terminated string.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "radix_strlen" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with s, i
        If byte is equal to 0:
            Return i
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return i
End Process

@Reasoning
Compute the length of the common prefix between two byte ranges.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Compare byte-by-byte while both have characters; stop at first
mismatch or end of either.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(min(a_len, b_len)).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "radix_common_prefix" takes a as Integer, a_off as Integer, a_len as Integer, b as Integer, b_off as Integer, b_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Let i be 0
    Let limit be a_len
    If b_len is less than limit:
        Set limit to b_len
    End If
    While i is less than limit:
        Let ab be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with a, a_off plus i
        Let bb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with b, b_off plus i
        If ab is not equal to bb:
            Return i
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return i
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: INSERT / LOOKUP
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Insert key->value, performing edge splitting when necessary. Walks
down the tree consuming bytes off the key:
- For each child edge of the current node, compute the common prefix.
- If common == 0: try next sibling. If none match the first byte,
  add a new edge containing the rest of the key.
- If common == edge_label_len: consume edge, advance current key
  offset, descend into edge's child node, continue outer loop.
- If common < edge_label_len AND common < remaining key: split the
  edge at 'common', creating an intermediate node, then add a new
  edge for the remaining key tail.
- If common == remaining key length AND common < edge_label_len:
  split the edge so the intermediate node holds the value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterative descent with explicit case handling at each step.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k) average, where k is key length.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "radix_insert" takes tree as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let klen be proc radix_strlen with key
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    Let k_pos be 0
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        If k_pos is equal to klen:
            Let had be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, 0, 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, 8, value
            If had is equal to 0:
                Let ec be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, ec plus 1
            End If
            Return 1
        End If
        Let first_byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with key, k_pos
        Let edge be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
        Let prev_edge be 0
        While edge is not equal to 0:
            Let label be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 8
            Let llen be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 16
            Let edge_first be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with label, 0
            If edge_first is equal to first_byte:
                Let cp be proc radix_common_prefix with key, k_pos, klen minus k_pos, label, 0, llen
                If cp is equal to llen:
                    Note: consume entire edge, descend
                    Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 0
                    Set k_pos to k_pos plus llen
                    Set edge to 0 minus 1
                    Note: marker to break the inner loop and continue outer
                Otherwise:
                    Note: edge_label has uncommitted tail; split the edge.
                    Let split_node be proc radix_node_create
                    If split_node is equal to 0:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                    Note: New tail-edge takes the leftover bytes of the old edge's label.
                    Let old_child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 0
                    Let tail_edge be proc radix_edge_create with old_child, label, cp, llen minus cp
                    If tail_edge is equal to 0:
                        proc deallocate from Layout with split_node
                        Return 0
                    End If
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with split_node, 16, tail_edge
                    Note: Replace the existing edge's child with split_node and shrink its label.
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with edge, 0, split_node
                    Note: Truncate the existing label to length cp.
                    Let new_label be proc allocate from Layout with cp plus 1
                    If new_label is equal to 0:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                    Let cpi be 0
                    While cpi is less than cp:
                        Let src_addr be label plus cpi
                        Let dst_addr be new_label plus cpi
                        Let bb be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with src_addr, 0
                        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with dst_addr, 0, bb
                        Set cpi to cpi plus 1
                    End While
                    Let term_addr be new_label plus cp
                    proc memory_set_byte from Memory with term_addr, 0, 0
                    proc deallocate from Layout with label
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with edge, 8, new_label
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with edge, 16, cp
                    Note: Now advance into split_node and continue with the
                    Note: remaining key suffix.
                    Set cur to split_node
                    Set k_pos to k_pos plus cp
                    Set edge to 0 minus 1
                End If
            End If
            If edge is equal to 0 minus 1:
                Note: break inner loop, continue outer
                Set edge to 0
            Otherwise:
                If edge is not equal to 0:
                    Set prev_edge to edge
                    Set edge to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 24
                End If
            End If
        End While
        If k_pos is less than klen:
            Note: no matching edge first byte - add a new edge holding the
            Note: remaining suffix.
            Let leaf be proc radix_node_create
            If leaf is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with leaf, 0, 1
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with leaf, 8, value
            Let new_edge be proc radix_edge_create with leaf, key, k_pos, klen minus k_pos
            If new_edge is equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with leaf
                Return 0
            End If
            Let old_first be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with new_edge, 24, old_first
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, 16, new_edge
            Let ec be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, ec plus 1
            Return 1
        End If
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Lookup value for key. Walks edges consuming key bytes; returns 0 if
absent.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
At each step, find the edge whose label starts with the current key
byte. Match the full label against the next len(label) key bytes; if
match, advance; else return 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "radix_lookup" takes tree as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let klen be proc radix_strlen with key
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    Let k_pos be 0
    While k_pos is less than klen:
        Let first_byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with key, k_pos
        Let edge be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
        Let found be 0
        While edge is not equal to 0:
            Let label be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 8
            Let llen be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 16
            Let edge_first be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with label, 0
            If edge_first is equal to first_byte:
                If k_pos plus llen is greater than klen:
                    Return 0
                End If
                Let cp be proc radix_common_prefix with key, k_pos, klen minus k_pos, label, 0, llen
                If cp is equal to llen:
                    Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 0
                    Set k_pos to k_pos plus llen
                    Set found to 1
                    Set edge to 0
                Otherwise:
                    Return 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Set edge to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 24
            End If
        End While
        If found is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End While
    Let has_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
    If has_value is equal to 1:
        Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 8
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Containment predicate distinguishing "absent" from "present with 0".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Same descent as lookup but returns 1 on terminal has_value flag.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "radix_contains" takes tree as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let klen be proc radix_strlen with key
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    Let k_pos be 0
    While k_pos is less than klen:
        Let first_byte be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with key, k_pos
        Let edge be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 16
        Let found be 0
        While edge is not equal to 0:
            Let label be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 8
            Let llen be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 16
            Let edge_first be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with label, 0
            If edge_first is equal to first_byte:
                If k_pos plus llen is greater than klen:
                    Return 0
                End If
                Let cp be proc radix_common_prefix with key, k_pos, klen minus k_pos, label, 0, llen
                If cp is equal to llen:
                    Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 0
                    Set k_pos to k_pos plus llen
                    Set found to 1
                    Set edge to 0
                Otherwise:
                    Return 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Set edge to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with edge, 24
            End If
        End While
        If found is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End While
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, 0
End Process
